&lt;pre&gt;I'm very excited to see this work proceeding and am looking forward to
being able to LGTM. A few requests before we get there:&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

   - From what I understand we still won't be spec-compliant
   for android:, drivefs:, steam:, chromeos-steam:, and materialized-view:.
   Can you add failing web platform tests for all of those cases, to ensure
   that we capture this non-compliance?
   - I don't understand the role of the scheme registry after we ship this
   change. What will it do? The doc says &quot;(TBD) Remove the Scheme Registry.
   This can be yet another non-trivial project. This document does not cover
   this task.&quot; Are there still web-exposed behaviors between non-registered
   and registered schemes? Is there a danger that people will add more schemes
   to the registry and cause URL parsing to change? Or is this purely about
   code cleanup as after this change the scheme registry is a no-op?
   - In general it would be great to have a section of the doc covering
   future work, such as fixing those exceptional schemes, removing the scheme
   registry, and anything else that you have in mind. In particular I'm
   interested in which of these future work projects have compat impacts so we
   can know how web developers might see URL parsing change in the future.




